HEADWORD: Tait
<hw>Tait</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A
small nocturnal and arboreal Australian marsupial (<spn>Tarsipes
rostratus</spn>) about the size of a mouse. It has a long muzzle, a long
tongue, and very few teeth, and feeds upon honey and insects. Called
also <altname>noolbenger</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

